debugBuild()

Description
    bool debugBuild([object $engine=NULL])
    Sets debugging to TRUE.
    
Parameters
    engine
	The engine object.
    
Return Values
    Returns a boolean value, indicating success or failure.
    
Examples
    <?php
	...
	// Setup debugging
	debugBuild($this);
	    if (debugNeeded("includes")) {
		debugDisplay("includes","\$cleanPost",1,"Contents of the \$cleanPost array.",$this->cleanPost);
	    }

            if (debugNeeded("includes")) {
		debugDisplay("includes","\$cleanGet",1,"Contents of the \$cleanGet array.",$this->cleanGet);
	    }
	...
    ?>

See Also
    engineCMS::__construct()
    debugNeeded()
